ch <i>machun</i>)."],"variants":[{"name":"Mason","meanings":["Transferred use of the surname, which originated in the early Middle Ages as an occupational name for a worker in stone, Old French <i>maçon</i> (of Germanic origin, connected with Old English <i>macian</i> ‘to make’)."]},{"name":"Machin","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Manuel, Juan, Jose, Carlos, Jorge, Mario, Miguel, Pedro, Blanca, Diego, Luis, Ramon.","English: variant of   Machen  . This is the more common form of the name in Britain and Ireland.","Spanish (<b>Machín</b>): probably a nickname from <i>machín</i> ‘boor, lout’, often applied to a blacksmith's apprentice."]},{"name":"Meacham","meanings":["English: variant of   Machen  . It may occasionally also be a variant of <b>Measham</b>, a habitational name from Measham in Leicestershire. The place takes its name from the river Mease (from Old English <i>mēos</i> ‘marsh, bog’) + Old English <i>hām</i> ‘village, homestead’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mädchen was born about 1135, in Heimbach, Düren, North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany. She married Eberhard I von Heimbach about 1155. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter."},"et":{"um 1135–":"umbes 1135–Surnud","1133–1217":"1133–1217","1155–1217":"1155–1217","1162–Female":"1162–Surnud","1135–Female":"1135–Surnud","1217":"1217","about 1162":"umbes 1162","1135":"1135","1155":"1155","1133":"1133","um 1135":"umbes 1135","um 1155":"umbes 1155","1162":"1162","UM 1115":"umbes 1115","Heimbach, Düren, North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany":"Heimbach, Düren, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Saksamaa","Heimbach Eifel Kreis Düren":"Heimbach, Düren, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Saksamaa","Heimbach, Düren, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Duitsland":"Heimbach, Düren, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"um 1135–":"noin 1135–Kuollut","1133–1217":"1133–1217","1155–1217":"1155–1217","1162–Female":"1162–Kuollut","1135–Female":"1135–Kuollut","1217":"1217","about 1162":"noin 1162","1135":"1135","1155":"1155","1133":"1133","um 1135"